      "description": {
        "localized_texts": [
          {
            "language_code": "en",
            "text": "UR-MU +N is a contemporary Art Museum that features nearly 70 artworks from a private art collection, Strategies of Dissent explores the art of protest and resistance from the 1990s to the present.Structured as a series of rhetorical and representational strategies.The exhibition invites us to discover the radical act of picturing, highlighting the role that artists have played in political movements in Malaysia and the region.Strategies of Dissent draws out these histories, challenging the preconception that spectacle is the sole marker of resistance."
          }
        ]
